{
  "texts": [
    "However, these metrics might not capture the full complexity or usefulness of a generated test case.",
    "Test Generation in a Regression Setting: In this paper, we operated under the assumption that the tests are generated within a regression setting, assuming the correctness of the underlying focal method implementation.",
    "As a result, our generated tests may not uncover any implementation bugs.",
    "This approach to testing also has limitations, particularly when the implementation of the focal method is not yet finalized, a scenario commonly encountered in continuous development environments.",
    "Our work relates to the following areas: Search Based Software Testing, Symbolic Test Generation, Test Generation with LLMs, and Hybrid LLM-SBST test generation."
  ]
}